    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras are navigating a disjointed slate today, forced to manage significant rainouts to core power hitters **Yordan Alvarez**, **Trea Turner**, and **Kyle Schwarber**. In their absence, the daily optimizer highlights **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (76.26) and **Junior Caminero** (74.22) as our premier starts. **Pete Crow-Armstrong** is the clear statistical anchor of the lineup; he benefits from a massive +19% SP skill boost against Waldron, and his elite sprint speed\u2014a necessity for our league-wide strategy\u2014is maximized by a dynamic platoon advantage that pushes his efficiency score deep into the strong territory. **Junior Caminero** provides excellent leverage in the #2 hole, where his ability to capitalize on the platoon advantage against Williams, G is amplified by his prime spot in the batting order.\n\nWhile **Kazuma Okamoto** (61.18) and **Gary Sanchez** (59.37) offer reliable production, the roster construction required some tough choices at the margins. **Dillon Dingler** (33.16) was the most difficult exclusion from the starting nine; despite his solid base projections, the optimizer penalized him heavily for the negative SP skill impact posed by Ritchie, ultimately dropping him well below our 40.0 floor. Elsewhere, **Caleb Durbin** (47.42) remains in the lineup despite a sluggish #9 spot in the order, as his utility remains high even in a neutral platoon setting. We are monitoring **Colt Keith** (46.51) closely; while he is currently an active start, the matchup against the sharp Ritchie presents a volatility risk that keeps his score hovering near the marginal threshold. We remain cautious with **Carson Benge** (50.74) as well, given the park factors slightly dampening his otherwise standard projection.",
